                                                                                                               RBI panel to vet key rates
          OUR BUREAU                              
	Mumbai, June 11: The Reserve Bank today set up a working group to review benchmark prime lending rates and suggest a mechanism for the pricing of floating rate loans, a move that would ensure better transparency in the fixation of interest rates on housing loans by banks.        
	The working group will suggest a suitable benchmark for floating rate loans in the retail segment, a central bank release said. Meanwhile, RBI governor Duvvuri Subbarao is likely to take charge of functions related to the framing of the monetary policy after Rakesh Mohan relinquished the office of deputy governor on Wednesday.        
	Mohan was in charge of monetary policy, financial markets, economic research and statistics, the secretarys department and communications. He is heading to Stanford University where he will be a consulting professor.         
	Reports say that chief economic adviser in the finance ministry Arvind Virmani is the frontrunner to replace Mohan.                                                                                                                                                                 
